</subtitle><entry><title type="html">Two trades</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/2020/12/17/EXL4DX.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Two trades" /><published>2020-12-17T20:40:00+11:00</published><updated>2020-12-17T20:40:00+11:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/2020/12/17/EXL4DX</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/2020/12/17/EXL4DX.html">&lt;p&gt;Hadn’t had a discretionary trade in a while. I took a couple of weeks off to go surfing. Took me another two weeks to find a spot where I felt comfortable having a crack. 4DX wasn’t that spot.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/assets/images/trades/2020-12-03-4DX.PNG&quot; alt=&quot;4DX&quot; title=&quot;4DX&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I bought for 2.59 on the day after that big volume bar on the 2nd of December. I thought I was getting in at a good price for a push to new highs. The thing could not find a buyer and I ended up closing it a couple days later at 2.39. What moved it on the 2nd was some fluff non-material announcement. Pretty happy I got out in hindsight. Couldn’t wait for a pullback in this situation. The sad thing is I was tossing up between this and ABR - similar setup:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/assets/images/trades/2020-12-03-ABR.PNG&quot; alt=&quot;ABR&quot; title=&quot;ABR&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Luckily for EXL though. A couple of days prior the stock ran when Biden got in and then there was a bit of an opportunistic placement. The cannabis theme kept developing and I was in on the day the WHO made some change to their classification of cannabis. The good thing about this trade was that EXL was happy to hold higher prices, a great sign of strength.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/assets/images/trades/2020-12-03-EXL1.PNG&quot; alt=&quot;EXL1&quot; title=&quot;EXL1&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Nothing happened until 12:30pm. A lot of doubt before then.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/assets/images/trades/2020-12-03-EXL2.PNG&quot; alt=&quot;EXL2&quot; title=&quot;EXL2&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Missed the capitulation through 30c. Was thinking “damn, it’s over already” on the morning of the 10th but decided to give it a bit of room given how things have been running in this market. Gave it one more day and it looked like there was some volume sell algo on the 11th with buyers holding off. Thought it would drift lower and it did. Now I have to think about getting back in.&lt;/p&gt;

